test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 1 == 40
 +  where 1 = <built-in function prod>([])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x70824cb85000>([40])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x70824cb85000> = [[1, 40], [1, 40, 1], [40], [40, 1], [1, 40], [1, 40, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x70824cb85000>([1, 40])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x70824cb85000> = [[1, 40], [1, 40, 1], [40], [40, 1], [1, 40], [1, 40, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x70824cb85000>([40, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x70824cb85000> = [[1, 40], [1, 40, 1], [40], [40, 1], [1, 40], [1, 40, 1], ...].count
